His face grim, Warden Duckworth ordered his car, then dashed from the office.\par
"Come on, Frank!" Joe cried, starting down the long, low-ceilinged corridor.\par
"I wonder how Turk ever got out," Frank said, racing after his brother.\par
Reaching the outer prison yard, they saw guards everywhere, on alert with rifles in case more of the prisoners should try to take advantage of the confusion and make a break.\par
"I was told," Duckworth said to the man at the gate, "that Turk may have escaped by jumping into a butcher's truck as it left the prison. Did you see which way the truck headed?"\par
"Yes, sir. North on Route 403. It was a National Meat truck."\par
Three emergency trucks came roaring to the gate from the prison garage, followed by the warden's\par
